        <mj-text css-class="article">
          <h2>Stuff &amp; Things</h2>
          <p>Our curated list of recent, suggested listening, reading and viewing.</p>

          <dl>
            <dt>
              <svg><use xlink:href="#article" /></svg> 
              <a href="https://www.wired.com/story/google-antitrust-lawsuit-search-results/">How Google Alters Search Queries to Get at Your Wallet</a>
            </dt>
            <dd>From Wired, testimony during Google's antitrust case has revealed that the company may be altering billions of queries a day to generate results that will get you to buy more stuff. Not that I trusted Google much before, but this goes beyond ... I'm just MAD now.</dd>

            <dt>
              <svg><use xlink:href="#youtube" /></svg> 
              <a href="https://youtu.be/UgqEqYjgUyI">The Art Collection of David Bowie</a>
            </dt>
            <dd>From Sotheby's Institute of Art, an interesting look at Bowie's art obsession.</dd>

            <dt>
              <svg><use xlink:href="#youtube" /></svg> 
              <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aC99lNQdNmA">A.I. Filmmaking Is Not The Future. It's a Grift.</a>
            </dt>
            <dd>A long, but worth it essay by film video-essayist Patrick H. Willems, about why AI is definitely not going to replace human creativity, and how "those [viral] A.I.-generated Wes Anderson parodies" are actually crap.</dd>
            <dd>Here's <a href="https://nebula.tv/videos/patrickhwillems-ai-filmmaking-is-not-the-future-its-a-grift">the video on Nebula</a>, a better place to watch it if you have the access.</dd>

            <dt>
              <svg><use xlink:href="#article" /></svg> 
              <a href="https://petapixel.com/2023/05/24/googles-ai-product-studio-removes-need-for-expensive-photographers/">Google's AI Product Studio Removes Need for "Expensive" Photographers</a>
            </dt>
            <dd>I have no words. I am just very disappointed in the world.</dd>
          </dl>
        </mj-text>        
